I have a clarification regarding Dependency Injection in Angular 2 . Here it goes.
Consider employee.ts
import { WebServices } from './web'; @Component({ selector : 'employee-dir', providers : [WebServices] }) export class EmployeeComponent { private _service : WebServices; constructor(_service : webServices) { this._service = _service; } getEmpCount() : number { return this._service.length; } }
In this example we have a parameterized constructor
constructor(_service : webServices) { this._service =_service; }
Normally in any programming language in C# or Java , we need to call class name with one parameter for invoking the constructor which accepts one parameter.
In C#, I would be doing
new EmployeeComponent(webServiceExample);
But I am not sure how this is executed in angular 2.
How do I pass webservice name as the first parameter of constructor from root module or from anywhere else?

